<subSubSection id="E17B2DA5FA9618AEFA750E079AA3A71D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8A9B3A3B939B2620AA479D170AC2AE6A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="028AEC38B8BB92D1706BF6C8A267BEAE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Named after J. R. Vockeroth in honor of his lifetime of work on 
<taxonomicName id="123A5A7F489BCFFDD372C3572E432AAA" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Syrphidae</taxonomicName>
and who was the first to recognize characters distinguishing this species from the sympatric 
<taxonomicName id="846646BBAB2E4DD2B755FE03A9E6F622" authority="Bigot, 1882" authorityName="Moran &amp; Skevington" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Giglio-Tos" baseAuthorityYear="1892" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Romaleosyrphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Romaleosyrphus arctophiloides" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctophiloides">
<emphasis id="9323B1E438F2B17BDEC7592F6B4CBB33" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Romaleosyrphus arctophiloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
many years ago.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
